{"cursor":"20996","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"During the 1950s, Solomon Asch conducted and published a series of laboratory\nexperiments that demonstrated the degree to which an individual's own opinions\nare influenced by those of a majority group. Asch, S.E.\n(1951). Effects of group pressure on the modification and distortion of\njudgments. In H. Guetzkow (Ed.), Groups, leadership and men(pp. 177â190).\nPittsburgh, PA:Carnegie Press. Asch, S.E. (1952b).\n\"Social psychology\". Englewood Cliffs,NJ:Prentice Hall. Asch, S.E. (1955). Opinions and social pressure. Scientific\nAmerican, 193, 35â35. Asch, S.E. (1956).\n[http://psycnet.apa.org/journals/mon/70/9/1/ Studies of independence and\nconformity. A minority of one against a unanimous majority]. Psychological\nMonographs, 70(9), 1â70. Together, these experiments are recognized as the\n'Asch conformity experiments' or the 'Asch Paradigm'. The methodology developed\nby Asch has been utilised by many researchers and the paradigm is in use in\npresent day social psychology. The paradigm has been used to investigate the\nrelationship between conformity and task importance, Milgram,\nS. (1961). [https://www.scientificamerican.com/article.cfm?id=milgram-nationality-\nconformity Nationality and conformity]. Scientific America, 205(6).\nage, Pasupathi, M (1999).\n[http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/10224640 Age differences in response to\nconformity pressure for emotional and nonemotional material]. Psychology and\nAging, 14(1), 170â4. gender, Cooper, H.M. (1979).\nStatistically combining independent studies: A meta-analysis of sex differences\nin conformity research. Journal of Personality and Social Psychology, 37,\n131â146. Eagly, A.H. (1978). Sex differences in\ninfluenceability. Psychological Bulletin, 85, 86â116. Eagly, A.H. & Carli, L. (1981).\n[http://psycnet.apa.org/journals/bul/90/1/1/ Sex of researchers and sex-typed\ncommunications as determinants of sex differences in influenceability: A meta-\nanalysis of social influence studies ]. Psychological Bulletin, 90(1),\n1â20. Bond, R. & Smith, P.B. (1996). [http://www.rad-\nford.edu/~jaspelme/_private/gradsoc_articles/individualism_collectivism/conform-\nity%20and%20culture.pdf Culture and conformity: A meta-analysis of studies using\nAsch's (1952b, 1956) line judgement task ]. Psychological Bulletin, 199(1),\n111â137. and culture.\n","linknr":288,"url":"Asch_conformity_experiments","recorded":1374543575,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Asch_conformity_experiments&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Asch_conformity_experiments&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Solomon_Asch","#cite_note-Asch1951-1","#cite_note-Asch1952b-2","#cite_note-Asch1955-3","#cite_note-Asch1956-4","/wiki/Social_psychology","/wiki/Conformity#Different_stimuli","#cite_note-Milgram-5","/wiki/Conformity#Age","#cite_note-Pasupathi-6","/wiki/Conformity#Gender","#cite_note-CooperHM-7","#cite_note-Eagly78-8","#cite_note-EaglyCarli-9","#cite_note-BondSmith-10","/wiki/Conformity#Culture","#cite_note-Milgram-5","#cite_note-BondSmith-10","#Initial_conformity_experiment","#Methodology","#Results","#Asch.27s_variations","#Interpretations","#Normative_influence